    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-03-02T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-03-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="30"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d30">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">579.6AE1/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-02T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 2, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 2—7:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>287. From Williamson and Kennedy. Embassy’s 283, March 1, 1 p.m.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d30fn5">Not printed.</note> Convention concerning exemptions for
                    aircraft fuel was <pb facs="0044" n="36" xml:id="pg_36"/> signed <hi
                        rend="italic">ad referendum</hi> last evening by the representatives of
                    principal powers including Germany and Italy, Japan not being represented. The
                    Ambassador signed in behalf of the United States. The French text alone is
                    authentic.</p>
                <p>Because of last minute amendments to article 4, made necessary by the adoption of
                    a single authentic text, there will be some delay in forwarding definitive text
                    of the convention.<note n="6" xml:id="d30fn6">The text of this convention is
                        published as British Cmd. 6001, Misc. No. 7 (1939): <hi rend="italic"
                            >International Conference for the Exemption from Taxation for Liquid
                            Fuel and Lubricants Used in Air Traffic, Final Act and Convention,
                            London, March 1, 1939</hi>. This convention was not submitted by the
                        President to the Senate of the United States for advice and consent to
                        ratification; it was not ratified by any of the other signatory powers, and
                        therefore did not enter into effect.</note> Copies of the uncorrected text
                    will be sent by <hi rend="italic">Queen Mary</hi> sailing March 3.</p>
                <p>Practically all the amendments proposed by the United States, in accordance with
                    the Department’s instruction dated January 27, 1939, were accepted by the
                    conference in one form or another. The proposed extensions outlined in the
                    Department’s 56 of January 21, 1 p.m., are incorporated in the form of
                    recommendations. [Williamson and Kennedy.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
